Subject: Re: [T2] Servicing Auto Tranny

On Tue, 23 Apr 2002, Mark Dominesey wrote:

got a 78 auto tranny and do this regularly

.  remove the 4 bolts an the four corners of the tranny pan
.  remove fill tube (catch tranny fluid in pan)
.  remove tranny pan, carefull of the rubber seal in the slot around the
edge, if this is avaliable anywhere I haven't found it, clean and reuse
.  underside of tranny there is a cover looks a bit like an apostrophe '
.  remove screw in this and clean, this is the filter, be careful
.  replace filter
.  replace cover
.  replace fill tube
refill and test drive

Bob


